text: Richland County is a county in the U.S. state of South Carolina. As of the 2020 census, 416,147 people lived there, making it the second-most populous county in South Carolina, after Greenville County. The county seat and largest city is Columbia, the state capital. The county was created in 1785. == References == == Other websites == * Richland County, South Carolina - Official Website Category:1785 establishments in South Carolina Category:South Carolina counties
